* file system cmd
ls -alh 
a- all file incluede hidden one start with .
l- show permissions owner size etc
h- human readbale means kb gb file

* disk usage
 for hole system - ds -h
 for specific folder - du -h

* system process 
ps aux
show hierachy
ps -axjf

* listning ports and connections
netstat -ltpn

* create new user with deafult setting
sudo useradd -m username

* change user password
sudo passwd username

* Delete user
sudo userdel -r username

* change user
su username

* list of group of given user
groups username

* create new group
groupadd grpname

add user to group
usermod -a -G grpname username

* package management
apt/apt-get

install
apt-get install fdisk

search 
apt search disk

remove
apt-get purge fdisk

* changing owner of file
chown root test.sh

changing groups
chown user:group test.sh
